[lesson]   Solution: **FIX_PLAN:** Edit `mllm_load_model` in `/root/.venv/lib/python3.12/site-packages/auto_round/utils/model.py` to wrap the `AutoProcessor.from_pretrained(...)` call (lines ~756-761) in a `try/except OSError` (plus `Exception` for robustness), and on failure set `processor = None`. The downstream MLLM compressor already handles `processor is None` correctly (`mllm_mixin.py:97` is guarded). This makes AutoRound able to quantize the LM backbone of any Qwen3.5-VL-style model whose HF repo omitted `preprocessor_config.json`, fixing the apodex case and similar future cases.;;**SMOKE_TEST:** `cd /root/.venv && python3 -c "from transformers import AutoProcessor; from auto_round.utils.model import mllm_load_model; import torch; model, proc, tok, imgp = mllm_load_model('dark-pen/apodex-1.0-0.8B-SFT-rebased'); print('proc=', proc, 'imgp=', imgp, 'tok=', type(tok).__name__); del model; print('OK')"`;;--;
